1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,333
<i> You shouldn't pick fights,</i>

2
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:13,733
<i>because it will reflect badly
on my family!</i>

3
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:14,900
<i> We already agreed</i>

4
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>you wouldn't leave Baby Jasmine
alone with Jobert,</i>

5
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> but you still did!</i>

6
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,167
<i> Bad!</i>

7
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,600
<i>- Bad!
- Jobert, that's enough.</i>

8
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:23,933
<i> Jobert! Stop it!</i>

9
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:25,067
<i>- I don't want this anymore!
- Jobert, what's wrong with you?</i>

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,067
<i> Cut it out! That's enough!</i>

11
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,300
<i> There's really no way to tell</i>

12
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,133
<i>when he's going to have
an episode.</i>

13
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:33,000
<i> You know what triggers him?</i>

14
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:36,233
<i>The nasty attitudes
of the people upstairs.</i>

15
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,300
<i> Where's Jobert?</i>

16
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:39,233
<i>He's still locked in his room,
Ma'am.</i>

17
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:42,100
<i>He keeps calling
for your mother.</i>

18
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:43,900
<i>Then why don't you
just bring him there?</i>

19
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:47,033
<i>So we can finally have
some peace and quiet here.</i>

20
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:49,833
<i> My heart breaks for my kids.</i>

21
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:52,500
<i>If only
I'd been a better mother...</i>

22
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:54,900
<i>I was too busy
putting myself first.</i>

23
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:58,033
<i>That's why Marj had no choice
but to bring him to the mansion.</i>

24
00:00:58,167 --> 00:01:00,367
<i> I'm going to be a dad!</i>

25
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,267
<i>Don't you feel sorry
for my brother?</i>

26
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,600
<i>You're going to lie to him
for the rest of your life.</i>

27
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:08,467
<i>You're safe from your wife
because of what I did.</i>

28
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:10,633
<i> You should be thanking me.</i>

29
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:13,067
<i>You won't be separated
from our child.</i>

30
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,533
<i>Your baby is looking healthy
at two months.</i>

31
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:16,967
<i>There's nothing wrong,
right, Doc?</i>

32
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:20,533
<i>I just want everything to be
perfect when she's born.</i>

33
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:24,367
<i>I have very big dreams for her.</i>

34
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:29,100
<i>Doc, I'm just worried
about my baby.</i>

35
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:35,967
I never miss a feeding,
but she's not gaining weight.

36
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:38,467
And her cough keeps coming back.

37
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:42,767
We detected signs
of mild respiratory distress.

38
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:45,867
And there's something else
we need to discuss.

39
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,600
Since your baby
was born premature,

40
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,300
we suspect she may have
bronchopulmonary dysplasia

41
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:52,700
or BPD.

42
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:56,400
I'm not familiar with that.

43
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,300
Is it dangerous?

44
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:02,867
BPD is a chronic lung condition
common in premature babies.

45
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:08,200
They get tired easily and
catch colds and coughs quickly.

46
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:10,533
And sometimes,
even pneumonia.

47
00:02:10,667 --> 00:02:12,100
So what can we do?

48
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:14,367
Is there any treatment?

49
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:17,600
We'll run more tests to be sure.

50
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:23,133
Most preemies outgrow
BPD as their lungs heal.

51
00:02:23,267 --> 00:02:25,000
But if she's not cared
for properly,

52
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:28,900
it can persist as she grows up.

53
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:34,500
Our poor baby.

54
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:37,733
Why do we have
to go through this?

55
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:35,567
Good morning, Daddy Greg.

56
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:39,400
How's my grandchild?

57
00:03:39,533 --> 00:03:42,467
Very healthy,
according to the doctor.

58
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,000
That's great. I'm relieved.

59
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:47,767
I just hope the child turns out
better than the father.

60
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,533
And by father...

61
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,333
I mean Edward.

62
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,300
Speaking of Edward,

63
00:03:57,433 --> 00:03:59,267
that's actually why I'm here.

64
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:06,900
I just want to remind you
about our agreement.

65
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:10,833
About investing in his start-up.

66
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:16,700
I haven't forgotten my promise.

67
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,300
I just want to be sure.

68
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,233
You know what?

69
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:30,767
When I first met you,
I was impressed.

70
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:33,200
I thought, for once,

71
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:36,967
Edward did the right thing
by choosing you.

72
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:40,900
But...

73
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,600
I was wrong about you.

74
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,900
You're materialistic...

75
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:52,700
just like the rest of them.

76
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:02,367
Say I'm after money.

77
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:05,533
Fine, I am.

78
00:05:05,667 --> 00:05:08,200
But I'm not doing this
for myself.

79
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,600
I'm securing my baby's future.

80
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:14,000
Your grandchild's future.

81
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:19,233
If being a good mother makes me
a bad person in your book,

82
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:22,033
then so be it.

83
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:49,500
Yolly, make sure the room
temperature stays at 24 degrees.

84
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:52,600
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Not too cold, not too warm.

85
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:58,767
And everyone needs to sanitize
before coming in.

86
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,200
I'll leave this right here.

87
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:01,900
Yes, Ma'am.

88
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:05,400
- We'll step out now.
- Okay, thanks.

89
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,433
Don't stress too much, okay?

90
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:16,133
Baby's going to be fine.

91
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:18,100
We'll get through this...

92
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:19,233
with her.

93
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,633
Hang on,
let me check her diaper.

94
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,933
Hi, Jasmine.

95
00:06:28,067 --> 00:06:30,600
Let's see if there's...

96
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:43,400
<i>I just wanted to share the first
picture of your future child.</i>

97
00:06:43,567 --> 00:06:45,667
<i>I'm sure she'll look like you
when she's born.</i>

98
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:52,833
Love?

99
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,767
Who's texting you?

100
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:02,133
<i> Yes, I understand.</i>

101
00:07:02,267 --> 00:07:05,367
I won't waste this opportunity.

102
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:12,000
Hon, who were you talking to?

103
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:18,167
It was dad.

104
00:07:20,367 --> 00:07:22,133
He wants to finance
my start-up.

105
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:25,267
Really?

106
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,233
That's good news, right?

107
00:07:28,267 --> 00:07:30,300
Then why don't you look happy?

108
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:32,167
I know dad.

109
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,333
I really know him.

110
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:39,000
He never gives anything without
wanting something in return.

111
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:41,600
But...

112
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:46,233
maybe this is his way of fixing
things between you two.

113
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:48,200
Maybe that's the trade-off.

114
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:49,667
Who knows?

115
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,767
I don't know.

116
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,867
I still don't trust
his intentions.

117
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:59,633
Love, who texted you?

118
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:02,800
Oh, no one. Just Gemma.

119
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:08,267
She's reminding me about
the real estate fair next week.

120
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,033
Oh, you know,
Thea texted me, too.

121
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,133
What?

122
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:16,333
- Really?
- Yeah.

123
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:18,200
Just checking in.

124
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:21,267
She's excited
about their baby.

125
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:25,067
Honestly, I'm excited, too.
Are you?

126
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,133
Why would you ask that?

127
00:08:28,267 --> 00:08:29,400
Of course.

128
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:33,233
I'm happy Jasmine's going
to have someone to play with.

129
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:36,333
They'll be like siblings.

130
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:40,600
We don't even know if
they're having a girl or a boy.

131
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,167
Right?

132
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,167
It's okay, Baby.

133
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:54,300
You're being too negative.

134
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:59,100
I think his heart's softening
because...

135
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:01,700
he's about to have a grandchild
with us.

136
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:04,400
Just give him a chance.

137
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,867
People can change.

138
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:11,467
You'll just stress yourself out
thinking the worst.

139
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:16,033
You're right.

140
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,700
Thank you, Hon.

141
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,533
Maybe this is the start
of a new life for us.

142
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:25,900
As a family.

143
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:39,267
<i> May Almighty God bless you,</i>

144
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,533
the Father, the Son,
and the Holy Spirit.

145
00:09:41,667 --> 00:09:45,367
May He dwell in this place
now and forever.

146
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,367
- Amen.
- Amen.

147
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,767
- Thank you, Father.
- Thank you.

148
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:55,767
Congratulations!

149
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,000
Congratulations!

150
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:02,067
- Congratulations!
- Thank you.

151
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:04,800
Congratulations!

152
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:06,300
- Hon.
- Charm.

153
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,800
- Thank you.
- Let's eat.

154
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:12,767
Come on, let's eat.

155
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,633
Charm, take care of them.

156
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:15,967
Hon.

157
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:20,933
Congratulations
on your new office.

158
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:22,733
Our office.

159
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:23,833
Hon.

160
00:10:23,967 --> 00:10:25,300
We're married.

161
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:28,300
What's mine is yours.

162
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:30,300
I won't say no,

163
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:32,100
as long as it's not debt.

164
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:36,667
Marj, where's your husband?

165
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:40,267
He's busy at work, Mom.
He couldn't make it.

166
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:45,700
But he sends his congratulations
and his apologies.

167
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:49,600
Maybe he just can't handle
seeing my business succeed.

168
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:52,200
Oh, stop.
I'm sure that's not true.

169
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,400
Besides, I'm here.
I'm so proud of you.

170
00:10:55,533 --> 00:10:58,067
Congratulations
on your new venture.

171
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,867
- Thank you, Mom.
- Oh, boy.

172
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,867
And of course,
my son's lucky charm.

173
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,133
That's why I'm fond of you.

174
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:09,667
My favorite daughter-in-law.

175
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:15,700
Now that you and your dad
are on good terms,

176
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:20,233
I think it's better
if you move into the mansion.

177
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:22,733
It's bigger,
there are more helpers.

178
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:25,300
Thea would be more comfortable
there.

179
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:30,067
She'll have help
after she gives birth.

180
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,767
I don't know, Mom.

181
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:35,667
It's not good for a baby
to be stuck in a condo.

182
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:38,833
At the mansion,
there's fresh air and nature.

183
00:11:38,967 --> 00:11:41,100
It'll be better
for your child.

184
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:45,033
I actually love that idea.

185
00:11:45,167 --> 00:11:48,133
And it would be nice
for the whole family

186
00:11:48,267 --> 00:11:51,800
- to live under one roof.
- See? She gets it.

187
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:55,267
Wouldn't that be nice, Marj?

188
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:59,233
When I give birth,
our babies can grow up together.

189
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:17,600
Love? I forgot to tell you.

190
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:19,500
Mom mentioned earlier

191
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:23,900
that she wants Edward and Thea
to move back in here.

192
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,400
What?

193
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:29,367
So we can all be together.

194
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:32,900
She thinks it'll be better
for the baby once it's born.

195
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:36,100
I don't think
that's a good idea.

196
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:38,967
Why not, Love?

197
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,800
I actually think it is.

198
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:44,400
Jasmine will have someone to
play with once Thea gives birth.

199
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:51,000
You haven't experienced
what this house feels like

200
00:12:51,133 --> 00:12:52,633
when dad's in a bad mood.

201
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:54,833
And when he and Edward
start fighting.

202
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:59,667
This is the quietest
it's ever been in this house.

203
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:02,500
I don't want
my brother coming back

204
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:07,000
just so he and dad can pick up
where they left off.

205
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,133
The...

206
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:12,933
All that resentment
between them.

207
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:16,800
So no,

208
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:20,767
I don't think it's a good idea
for him to move back.

209
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:32,900
Well, I just hope you
and your family work things out

210
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:35,033
and live together again.

211
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:37,833
You know, Love...

212
00:13:37,967 --> 00:13:40,900
that's what I pray for
for our family.

213
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:47,900
I'm just going to check
on the baby.

214
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,767
She needs to eat.

215
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,633
Jasmine...

216
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:02,000
Baby...

217
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,600
Time for milk.

218
00:14:05,767 --> 00:14:07,100
Jasmine?

219
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:08,667
Jasmine?

220
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:11,533
Love!

221
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,867
- Love.
- What? What's wrong?

222
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:16,200
She's not breathing.

223
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:19,400
She's not breathing!

224
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:20,467
- Love...
- Come on, come on!

225
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,000
Call Oscar!

226
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:24,300
- Tell him to get the car ready!
- Let's go!

227
00:14:24,433 --> 00:14:25,633
Love!

228
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,467
Is she okay?

229
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:39,233
Nurse! Nurse! What happened?

230
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:41,567
- She has trouble breathing.
- This way, hurry.

231
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:45,100
Doc! We have a patient!

232
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,400
Jasmine...

233
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:50,700
Baby...

234
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,233
Baby...

235
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:55,733
Doc, please don't give up
on my child.

236
00:14:55,867 --> 00:14:57,033
Jasmine...

237
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,933
Don't worry, Love.
She's going to be fine.

238
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,967
Love, can you bring the rest
of the baby's things here?

239
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:18,067
The doctor said she needs
to stay confined for a few days.

240
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:21,067
Okay, okay.

241
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,100
I love you. Be careful.

242
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,533
- Marj.
- Mom.

243
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,400
Marj.

244
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:31,933
Marj, what happened
to Jasmine?

245
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:35,733
She has pneumonia, Mom.
Because of her BPD.

246
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:40,667
That's the lung condition she
has because she was premature?

247
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,200
Yes, Mom.

248
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:46,400
And I've been doing everything
to keep her safe.

249
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:48,933
I give her
all her medicines on time.

250
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:50,900
I take care of her. I watch her.

251
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,267
So why is this happening?
Why isn't she getting better?

252
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,900
- Marj.
- Mom, what am I doing wrong?

253
00:15:56,033 --> 00:15:58,267
- What am I missing?
- Marj...

254
00:15:59,267 --> 00:16:02,933
stop that. Don't talk like that.

255
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:09,167
You haven't done anything wrong.
This isn't your fault.

256
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:14,233
There are just things in life
you can't control.

257
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:19,767
What matters
is that you don't give up.

258
00:16:20,933 --> 00:16:24,733
And I know you'll never
give up on Jasmine.

259
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,333
Where did they take the child?

260
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:12,633
They just brought her
to the lab for tests.

261
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:15,867
This is your fault!

262
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:19,733
I know you've been
neglecting our grandchild.

263
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:21,233
That's why this happened!

264
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,633
Regina, don't make a scene here.

265
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:25,867
It's true!

266
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,333
If she had taken better care
of Jasmine,

267
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:29,200
this wouldn't have happened!

268
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:34,067
Please don't be unfair
to my wife.

269
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,300
She's doing everything
she can for our baby.

270
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:37,700
It's not enough!

271
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:43,300
Is it still not enough
that I gave up my career

272
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:46,433
to focus on our child?

273
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,667
Is it not enough
that I sent my brother away

274
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,833
just to protect Jasmine?

275
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:55,033
Don't throw that in our faces.

276
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:58,200
That's your responsibility.
You're the mother.

277
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,967
I didn't "just have a baby,"
Mom.

278
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:06,500
All I'm asking is,
please don't blame me.

279
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:09,433
Don't act like I wanted this.

280
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:11,267
You're a mother, too.

281
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:15,000
You should be the first one
to understand me.

282
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:19,467
So please, don't accuse me
of being a careless mother.

283
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,467
Don't give me that drama!

284
00:18:32,067 --> 00:18:33,400
All you ever have are excuses!

285
00:18:34,867 --> 00:18:37,500
If anything bad happens
to my grandchild,

286
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:39,333
I will never forgive you.

287
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,100
Are you really not
going to stop?

288
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:46,333
Don't embarrass me, Regina.

289
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:49,533
Don't push me
until I lose my patience.

290
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:55,400
Dad. Dad, Mom.

291
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:58,567
Please don't add to our stress.

292
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:01,200
Let's not start blaming
each other.

293
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:04,033
We all want the same thing.

294
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:06,100
For Jasmine to get better.
Right?

295
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:11,533
Mom, I'm sorry.

296
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:15,267
I just got carried away.

297
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:22,667
Let's not make this bigger
than it is, Regina.

298
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,900
Your daughter-in-law
already apologized.

299
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:26,400
What now?

300
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,100
I'm sorry, too.

301
00:19:33,867 --> 00:19:35,233
I raised my voice.

302
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:42,500
Can we just be united?

303
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:49,067
That's all we want, right?
For Jasmine to get through this.

304
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:02,333
Wow, look at this.
Fancy snacks and everything.

305
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,433
Even plated nicely!

306
00:20:04,567 --> 00:20:06,000
Of course.

307
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,267
Edward's dad gives me
a pretty generous allowance,

308
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:10,233
so I can buy
whatever I want.

309
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:14,733
All the snacks I used to eat
as a kid, before we went broke,

310
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:16,933
I finally get to eat them again.

311
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:18,300
But you know what?

312
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:20,700
Since I haven't had these
in so long,

313
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:23,433
my stomach's kind of cramping.

314
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,533
Wait a second.

315
00:20:27,667 --> 00:20:30,833
I thought the money his dad
gave you was for the business?

316
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,233
It is.

317
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:34,433
But obviously,
I took a little cut for myself.

318
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,933
You think I wouldn't?

319
00:20:37,067 --> 00:20:38,833
Girl, you're living the dream!

320
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:40,667
Even if you stop working,

321
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:43,000
you and your baby are set
for life.

322
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:46,700
And I'm sure Edward's business
is going to take off.

323
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:51,400
I mean, you've got everything!
You're so lucky, girl!

324
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:52,867
You know what, Lalaine?

325
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,800
I don't have everything yet.

326
00:20:55,933 --> 00:20:57,133
What?

327
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:05,800
Hey!

328
00:21:05,933 --> 00:21:07,333
Don't tell me
after all this time,

329
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:08,567
you still have feelings for him?

330
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:10,967
You are something else.

331
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:19,433
Wait, are you going into labor?

332
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:21,067
Hey!

333
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:36,667
Marj, thank God
Jasmine's stable now.

334
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:41,567
<i>I can finally breathe a little.</i>

335
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:45,867
But Marj is still worried sick.

336
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:48,533
Love, it's hard to relax.

337
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:51,033
What if she has another attack?

338
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:54,033
I think
that's just how women are.

339
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:56,700
Always worrying.

340
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,633
I'll just take this call.

341
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,400
Hello, Mom?

342
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,167
<i> Thea just gave birth, Pao.</i>

343
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:10,867
<i>She's at the same hospital
where Jasmine is.</i>

344
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,433
<i> Your dad and I are on our way.</i>

345
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,300
<i> We'll see you there.</i>

346
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:25,267
Love, what did mom need?

347
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:33,000
She said Thea gave birth.
She's here.

348
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:35,900
Same hospital.

349
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:37,800
Let's stop by and see them.

350
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:40,633
Mom's here anyway.
She can watch the baby.

351
00:22:43,167 --> 00:22:44,933
Love, maybe not right now.

352
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:47,567
Let's just let them enjoy
their baby first.

353
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,767
Love, just for
a little while.

354
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:53,400
Edward was there for me
when I gave birth.

355
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:55,633
And Thea stayed by my side.

356
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:58,733
I just want to return the favor,
even if it's just a quick visit.

357
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,933
The nurse asked me
to go to the station.

358
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:05,900
I need to sign some forms.

359
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:08,500
If you want, you can go ahead.

360
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:10,067
Okay.

361
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,333
I'll be quick.

362
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:13,867
Mom, can you watch
the baby for a bit?

363
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,800
Of course.

364
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:16,733
All right, Love.
I'll be right back.

365
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:30,433
So cute.

366
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:31,733
She looks like an angel, right?

367
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:35,100
Yeah. You love daddy, don't you?

368
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:37,367
Look at those rosy cheeks.

369
00:23:39,667 --> 00:23:41,500
She's so adorable!

370
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:42,700
Hello.

371
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:45,567
- Hi, Marj.
- How's the new mommy?

372
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:51,400
Oh, Marj, mom mentioned
you and Baby Jasmine were here.

373
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:53,567
- How is she?
- She's okay.

374
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,367
She's stable now.

375
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:58,000
You don't have to worry anymore.

376
00:23:59,233 --> 00:24:01,033
Congratulations
on the new baby.

377
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:03,067
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

378
00:24:04,267 --> 00:24:05,733
Do you want to hold her?

379
00:24:07,267 --> 00:24:09,567
- Are you sure?
- Of course.

380
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,300
- Go on, try.
- Okay.

381
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,933
Hello.

382
00:24:17,067 --> 00:24:18,033
Sorry.

383
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:21,200
Jasmine was really sensitive
when I gave birth.

384
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:23,700
I couldn't just let anyone
hold her.

385
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:26,100
Hi, Baby.

386
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:28,900
Hello.

387
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:31,100
I'm your Aunt Marj.

388
00:24:31,233 --> 00:24:34,700
Mom to your cousin and
future best friend, Jasmine.

389
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:37,500
Hi!

390
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:42,200
Wow, she's so beautiful.

391
00:24:43,067 --> 00:24:45,333
She's just as beautiful
as Jasmine.

392
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:50,033
Of course they are.

393
00:24:50,167 --> 00:24:51,933
They're sisters.

394
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,233
How's your child?

395
00:25:01,367 --> 00:25:02,600
Jasmine's doing okay.

396
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:05,900
I'll watch her tonight
so Marj can rest.

397
00:25:06,267 --> 00:25:08,867
At least you know which child
I'm talking about, Paolo.

398
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,600
Because she's
your only child.

399
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:12,933
The baby.

400
00:25:13,067 --> 00:25:14,333
Why?

401
00:25:14,467 --> 00:25:17,100
She kind of looks like
Sir Paolo when he was a baby.

402
00:25:17,467 --> 00:25:20,067
What's so wrong with stealing a
little moment like this, right?

403
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:21,800
Paolo, you're her father.

404
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:23,467
Who? You?

405
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:24,633
You know what?

406
00:25:24,767 --> 00:25:29,233
I hope you're as strong
and understanding as I am.

407
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:32,300
Greg had other women before.

408
00:25:32,433 --> 00:25:34,533
Now we're the same, Marjorie.

409
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:37,233
So you'd better start accepting

410
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,267
that you have to share
your husband.

411
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:43,367
It's not that I don't
want them to stay here.

412
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:47,267
It's just that
it's complicated.

413
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,300
- Greg!
- Dad!

414
00:25:48,433 --> 00:25:52,000
We need to get them a condo
or an apartment.

415
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:54,867
They can't stay here
in our house.

416
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,533
We'll step away for now, dear.

417
00:25:56,667 --> 00:25:58,000
So we can grow stronger.

418
00:25:58,133 --> 00:26:01,433
So we can prove we deserve this.

419
00:26:01,567 --> 00:26:05,767
And one day, we'll take back
everything that's ours.

420
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:08,100
Ash, where are uncle and auntie?

421
00:26:13,567 --> 00:26:15,300
Hi, Marj!

422
00:26:19,833 --> 00:26:21,633
Don't you miss me, Paolo?

423
00:26:21,767 --> 00:26:23,967
You don't have to avoid me.

424
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:25,833
Or Ashley.

425
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:28,233
I'm sure you miss your child,
too.

426
00:26:28,667 --> 00:26:30,233
What's going on?

427
00:26:30,367 --> 00:26:32,367
Are you two fighting?
